#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.68"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.68:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.68:0.2"
msgid "7. Pattakammavagga "
msgstr "7. Deeds of Substance "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.68:0.3"
msgid "68. Devadattasutta "
msgstr "68. Devadatta "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.68:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate acirapakkante devadatte. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain, not long after Devadatta had left. "

msgctxt "an4.68:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā devadattaṃ ārabbha bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha spoke to the mendicants about Devadatta: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.68:1.3"
msgid "“attavadhāya, bhikkhave, devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi. "
msgstr "“Possessions, honor, and popularity came to Devadatta for his own ruin and downfall. "

msgctxt "an4.68:1.4"
msgid "Parābhavāya, bhikkhave, devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.68:2.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kadalī attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti; "
msgstr "It’s like a banana tree, "

msgctxt "an4.68:2.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.68:3.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, veḷu attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti; "
msgstr "or a bamboo, "

msgctxt "an4.68:3.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.68:4.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, naḷo attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti; "
msgstr "or a reed, all of which bear fruit to their own ruin and downfall … "

msgctxt "an4.68:4.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.68:5.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, assatarī attavadhāya gabbhaṃ gaṇhāti, parābhavāya gabbhaṃ gaṇhāti; "
msgstr "It’s like a mule, which becomes pregnant to its own ruin and downfall. "

msgctxt "an4.68:5.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādīti. "
msgstr "In the same way, possessions, honor, and popularity came to Devadatta for his own ruin and downfall. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an4.68:6.1"
msgid "Phalaṃ ve kadaliṃ hanti, "
msgstr "The banana tree is destroyed by its own fruit, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.68:6.2"
msgid "phalaṃ veḷuṃ phalaṃ naḷaṃ; "
msgstr "as are the bamboo and the reed. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.68:6.3"
msgid "Sakkāro kāpurisaṃ hanti, "
msgstr "Honor destroys a sinner, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.68:6.4"
msgid "gabbho assatariṃ yathā”ti. "
msgstr "as pregnancy destroys a mule.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.68:6.5"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
